  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Season the <strong>chicken thigh skins</strong> with <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken</strong>, skin-side down and cook for 10 min</p><p>Once the chicken skin is crispy, transfer it to a plate, skin-side up, and reserve the pan for later</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1829.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1829.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1829.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1829.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1829.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and halve the <strong>shallots</strong></p><p>Peel the<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a pot over a low heat with 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>halved shallots</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>star anise</strong>, <strong>bay leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</span></strong> and cook for 20 min or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: the milk only needs to simmer gently</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1829.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1829.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1829.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1829.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1829.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Cut the <strong>parsnip<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (skin on) into rounds</p><p>Cut the<strong> carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (skin on) into rounds</p><p>Rip the leaves off the <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
